{
  "texts": [
    "We propose a vanilla planning approach that evaluates and predicts the consequences of executing each top k action and introduces a plan evaluator to make final decisions; a sample prompt template can be found in C.",
    "Planning Using the readable current observation, game history, game rules, and valid actions picked by the action recommender, we prompt LLMs to create text-based plans:",
    "i.e., O plan ∼ F plans θ.",
    "The vanilla planning approach assumes a uniform marginal distribution for adversaries' and allies' actions, and it can be regarded as a zero-order ToM, denoted as F zero-plan θ.",
    "Evaluator To evaluate each plan's potential success, the plan evaluator will predict win rates for each plan with readable context Obs r, His r, game rule and then recommend the best action:"
  ]
}